attributes.label: Start - Her one day trip to Misora
attributes.characterDialogue: My weekend was unfortunately not that great. I went on a one-day trip to Misora. With my <style="Link">Annoying Husband</style>. Just kidding, he is great.  You wonder why it was bad? So, we stayed at this very ugly and chaotic <style="Link">Hotel</style>. And honestly, I don't know about you but I absolutely hate chaos. On top of that, we didn't get any food there, so we had to eat in the Local <style="Link">Bad Restaurants</style>.

attributes.label: Rejected from Hotel
attributes.characterDialogue: We originally wanted to got to a Hotel, famous for it’s architecture, but when we called them and asked for a room, they denied us the stay. That is completely ridiculous. We even called two days in advance! Just wow. Do they even know <style="Link">who I am</style>. Do they think I’m <style="Link">too poor</style> to effort their hotel?!?!?! Denying an architecture fan <style="Link">like myself</style> that sight is completely inhumane.

attributes.label: Restaurant "Above the skies"
attributes.characterDialogue: Hmmm "Above the Clouds" Now that you mention it, That reminds me of this one Restaurant in Misora called "Above the skies". Their name is <style="Link">weird</style>, because when I was there they only served sandwiches. Like why call yourself "Above the skies" then, how am I suppposed to understand what they are selling?

attributes.label: City Hall
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh Heavens, don't get me started on the CiTy hALl. That place was a joke in off itself. We passed through there and it was so chaotic. Apparently, it's a place of community, where the people of Misora can come together, but for me it just looked like a collection of <style="Link">poor people</style>. And <style="Link">the government</style> calls That a "City Hall" unbelievable. A <style="Link">Lady of Class</style> like me would never go there voluntarily. If only we would have know.

attributes.label: The Viewing Platform
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh yes the Viewing Platform, When I was there, it was actually quite nice, because there finally was proper seating. My feet were <style="Link">hurting so much</style> from that horrible trip up with all those <style="Link">small rocky pathways</style>. I quickly left though, these <style="Link">annoying children</style> up there were just too much.

attributes.label: Shark Pound
attributes.characterDialogue: The Shark Pound was interesting. Apparently, it was built as a kind of turning point for boats driving through the canals of Misora, back when the plan was still to have more than two. Now it's kind of there, not getting any real use... We actually had a great idea to properly use this place: they should just build a beach here, the <style="Link">actual beach</style> is too far anyways. Why its called Shark Pound I have no idea, the city is just full of <style="Link">weird names</style>, like that <style="Link">Duckling Lake</style>, and those <style="Link">weird Boat Tours</style> too.

attributes.label: Coffee Shop
attributes.characterDialogue: Right, the Coffe Shop. You know, I know how to make good coffee, because I like getting up <style="Link">Early</style> at home and watching all the <style="Link">Hot Boys</style> do their Workouts in the Park, heh. From the balcony though, I don't really like <style="Link">Greenery</style>. So yeah I know what good coffee is, but this mass production, eh. <style="Link">Quality over Quantity</style>, I always say.

attributes.label: Greenery
attributes.characterDialogue: I have to say one thing I liked about Misora was all of the greenery and parks..... If we could have actually gone into them. But no, for some reason the city thinks it's a great idea to <style="Link">cut those off</style> with a big ass fence. <style="Link">What a Trip</style> huh. I would have loved to get in there and get some snippets of some rare plants. You know you can regrow most <style="Link">house plants</style> from getting even the tiniest piece of them? Of course, you don't. It's called propagation, you're welcome.

attributes.label: Harbor
attributes.characterDialogue: Of course we avoided the Harbor too. That jucky smell from <style="Link">that market</style> really contaminants the entire area. Also if I can avoid being around <style="Link">poor people</style> I will do that of course. Oh heavens, and don't get me started on <style="Link">the noise</style>, like build your ships quieter! Jesus. But it's kind of that <style="Link">the garden centre</style> is also in this area. I would have liked to go there.

attributes.label: Fish & Crab Market
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh yes we went past this Fish and Crab Market and the smell of those <style="Link">disgusting Ocean Animals</style> was horrible. Apparently, it has the largest tuna can collection in the world. I don't believe that for a second. We didn't go of course. You know those are the places where all the <style="Link">scammers</style> and <style="Link">Poor People</style> are! I only trust the <style="Link">real stores</style> of course.

attributes.label: Surfing Club
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh yes I love Surfing Clubs and seeing all those Hot Surfer Guys <style="Link">on the beach</style>. Really a treat for the eyes. If you know what I mean haha. The surfer guys in Misora were especially muscular, I just couldn't help but whistle at them. Then my husband got mad for some reason? Like am I not allowed to whistle anymore? Honestly I think I with <style="Link">my beauty</style> I could definitely join a surfer club and get all the boys. I'm <style="Link">still young</style> after all.

attributes.label: Horrible Trip
attributes.characterDialogue: To sum it all up, the trip was horrible! First I got <style="Link">Sick</style> from the terrible food, combined with a boat ride with one of the most incompetent captains I have ever met. Even my husband could do that better. On top of that, I <style="Link">Couldn't Sleep</style> all night! But not because of my mind! I meditate a lot and therefore live in perfect Edu..Eudaimoni...! Oh and then there was all the <style="Link">Discrimination</style>! No one respects a successful Lady. Sometimes I think I'm too kind to people...

attributes.label: Restricted Parks
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :(, here is a Summary: All of those restricted areas in Misora at the City Hall and at the Hotel were so annoying! They were rejected both times from entering. Unbelievable! She isn't one of those poor people and shouldnt't be treated like that and even after she explained them for 10 minutes that they should still be permitted to enter, they still didn't let them in. Then they had to walk all the way around.

attributes.label: No meal plans in the Hotel
attributes.characterDialogue: It is unbelievable that the Hotels in Misora don't offer any food! That is a total <style="Link">Scam</style>. And being forced to eat all that horrible food at those <style="Link">Local Restaurants</style> just further <style="Link">Ruined Everything</style>. The <style="Link">Original Hotel</style> that we wanted to go to would have never done something like this. I still don't understand why they would reject such important guests like us. Their loss!

attributes.label: Special Services for Cozy Camping
attributes.characterDialogue: The Cozy Camping had so many special services, that were simply not available for me. That was so discriminating! They had a private <style="Link">Boat Tour</style> and also a<style="Link">Private Gondola</style> that would have been the perfect way to get up to <style="Link">Mount Doom</style>. Well, at least our Hotel didn't have that many <style="Link">Annoying Children</style>, hah.

attributes.label: Noise
attributes.characterDialogue: Ohh, the Noise. I have very sensitive ears, and all those loud <style="Link">Children</style> there and my <style="Link">Husband</style> on top of that. That was too much. I felt so <style="Link">Discriminated</style>! If you were as unique of a person as I am, you would understand what I am talking about. Everything is always made for the average people. It's so unfair, just a <style="Link">Horrible Experience</style>.

attributes.label: Bought Gem Jewelry
attributes.characterDialogue: I bought the most amazing jewelry in Misora. It was so expensive but I look absolutely <style="Link">Beautiful</style> with it. My husband said I didn't need it, but what does he know? They had some real <style="Link">Rarities</style> there. You probably never heard of them but I knew exactly how much they were worth and knew that was something I needed to <style="Link">Bring Home</style>.

attributes.label: Not needingPublic Transport
attributes.characterDialogue: Public transport? What is that? As a <style="Link">Lady of Class</style> and dont need to use that service. You know that busses are actually the number one place to get <style="Link">pickpocketed</style> at.  So I'm of course never using the public transport. We made one singular exception <style="Link">in Misora</style> since walking to the city centre, <style="Link">while hungry</style> would have been ridiculous.

attributes.label: Style Boutiques
attributes.characterDialogue: Shopping in the local boutiques really made the whole trip worth it! <style="Link">Beauty</style> and looks are just so important to invest into! It was still <style="Link">Early Morning</style> when we got there, but the <style="Link">Sun</style> was already burning. At least we got there before all those annoying tourists so I had the stores all to myself. Even though I spend most of my time looking for the right address. You cant find anything there with those strange <style="Link">Street Names</style>. Do they really think that is funny?

attributes.label: Busses
attributes.characterDialogue: In the morning we took one of those <style="Link">City Info</style> bus tours to explore the city. Of course, it was late. Typical. But at least we were able to take a look at a beach right next to the bus station.The tour provided informative insights into the city's history but the constant <style="Link">Noise</style> from other passengers combined with my husband complaining about getting <style="Link">No Sleep</style>, made it impossible to fully enjoy the experience.

attributes.label: Bad Local Restaurants
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh yeah, the Restaurants really turned it into a <style="Link">Horrible Trip</style>! But still, we wanted to give them a chance, hah. I remember a <style="Link">Coffee Shop</style> a <style="Link">Seafood Restaurant</style> another <style="Link">Restaurant</style> before returning back to the Hotel, and this other one in the mountains. But yeah, anyways have I told you about the <style="Link">Hot Boys</style>?

attributes.label: Ocean annoying
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh yes I just hate the ocean. That’s why I also hate <style="Link">Boat Tours</style>! People say the sound is “relaxing”. I say otherwise. I just hear <style="Link">Noise</style>, Screams of <style="Link">Annoying Children</style> and the Ocean? Sounds the same to me.

attributes.label: Galleries
attributes.characterDialogue: Since there was no need to go into the <style="Link">Modern Art Museum</style>, we wanted to go to some of the local galleries, but the first one we went to was closed! Do these people even know what <style="Link">Getting Up Early</style> is? But yeah, since it was closed, we immediately headed to another, said to be in the shopping district, at least we could go into some <style="Link">Stores</style> on the way

attributes.label: The great view
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh the view from the <style="Link">Viewing Platform</style> was just amazing, you could so much from the city, like the <style="Link">Cathedral</style> on the Hill, <style="Link">The Shark Pound</style>, and even <style="Link">my Kingdom</style> sitting on top of the ocean. Absolutely divine.

attributes.label: Boat Tours
attributes.characterDialogue: Apparently Misora has a lot of different Boat Tours, which we would have <style="Link">loved to know</style> more about when we went there. But honestly looking back, the only thing we got out of those Tours anyways was getting <style="Link">seasick</style>. At least I didn’t throw up like my husband. Oh, and one good thing was that it was a bit cooler on the ocean than on the land. Though the <style="Link">midday sun</style> was already over anyways.

attributes.label: All  those small walkways
attributes.characterDialogue: These small rocky pathways were just the worst. When I had to go up the <style="Link">Mount Doom</style> on those pathways and see all of <style="Link">those Gondolas</style> going up and down. I really started questioning myself why I didn’t just take them instead. Those pathways were just way <style="Link">too much walking</style>. Who thought these paths were a good idea? Probably <style="Link">the government</style> again.

attributes.label: a fan of architecture
attributes.characterDialogue: Architecture is one of my hobbies. Misora was supposed to have beautiful architecture, but really it was not even close. The churches were definitely impressive but that is always the case for <style="Link">religious sites</style>. The <style="Link">City Hall</style> was disappointing at best. Quite <style="Link">the scam</style> actually

attributes.label: Stores
attributes.characterDialogue: Yes wow, the premium stores in the shopping district were absolutely divine. As a true <style="Link">appreciator for beauty</style>  I know when something is <style="Link">rare</style> and worth buying. And all of these <style="Link">Gem Jewels</style> definitely were!

attributes.label: Beaches
attributes.characterDialogue: When we were walking along the Beach, I though “Hey, why don’t walk with our feet the <style="Link">cooling water</style>”. Maybe we could also find some <style="Link">rare</style> Seashells, but then I remembered those disgusting algae at <style="Link">Algea Bay</style> and thought “Yeah, No way”. This also concluded my plan to <style="Link">build my mansion</style> on a beach

attributes.label: Seafood Restaurant
attributes.characterDialogue: We went to this seafood restaurant near the beach, together. It was very expensive, which wasn't the problem because I mean, I have the <style="Link">Money</style>. But the food...just the thought of eating slimy <style="Link">Ocean Animals</style> is so disgusting. But you know, there were <style="Link">No meal</style> plans in the Hotel, so we had to eat the local junk.

attributes.label: Appreciating Beauty
attributes.characterDialogue: You know I consider myself as a True Appreciator of Beauty. I can identify beauty in everything it’s in and if it’s not I immediately take notice. That’s a talent of mine. That is why I love <style="Link">Vintage Cars</style> and Art. As well as visiting <style="Link">Style Boutiques</style> and <style="Link">Galleries</style>. It even goes as far as to discover the <style="Link">best-looking men</style> out there.

attributes.label: The Cathedral on the hill
attributes.characterDialogue: The cathedral on hill was really something, I would have loved to know more about it, but <style="Link">the Bus</style> didn’t even mention it, Unbelievable. As a <style="Link">fan of architecture</style> I respect the incredible <style="Link">Display of Wealth</style>

attributes.label: Hurting Feet
attributes.characterDialogue: From all that <style="Link">Hiking</style> my feet hurt so much. An <style="Link">important lady</style> like me shouldn’t have to worry about something like that. What a <style="Link">horrible trip</style>.

attributes.label: Hot Boys
attributes.characterDialogue: Hmm, yes the Hot Boys in Misora. That's one good thing about <style="Link">The scorching sun</style>. Especially the ones from the <style="Link">Surfing Club</style>, in their swimming shorts.  They all looked like they were modeling for the local <style="Link">Style Boutiques</style>. Hmm, I love vacations.

attributes.label: Climate Activists
attributes.characterDialogue: I hate those climate activists always spraying tomato sauce over <style="Link">rare</style> and important items. So that's what the <style="Link">young generation</style> is all about now? Using <style="Link">Public Transport</style> and destroying rare items?

attributes.label: Hotel: The Pearl
attributes.characterDialogue: I’m not a fan of the Hotel "The Pearl", with their fancy-ass <style="Link">greenery</style> anymore, first they deny me the stay and then they didn't even let me pass through to the other side. Do they even know <style="Link">who I am</style>? Did they even realise what a long path we needed to take around the property and that it would completely <style="Link">destroy the trip</style> for me?

attributes.label: Why it's called Platypus Beach
attributes.characterDialogue: The city names in general are just <style="Link">super weird</style> with <style="Link">fish names</style> for Boat Tours, like am I twelve? But I have a theory why the Platypus Beach is called like that. When I went there, I saw a bunch of little platypuses hiding from the <style="Link">scorching midday sun</style>. Looks like there is an infestation of platypuses there.

attributes.label: Getting up early
attributes.characterDialogue: I ALWAYS get up early. Especially on vacation! That way I am able to see as much as possible! But sleeping with all that <style="Link">Noise</style> in Misora, was not easy anyways. So even my husband got up early and we managed to take the first <style="Link">Bus</style> towards the city center.

attributes.label: Cozy Camping Gondola
attributes.characterDialogue: You know I read about the <style="Link">Gondola</style> for the <style="Link">Cozy Camping</style> people, but only for them. Do they even know that is <style="Link">Discrimination</style>? They are taking away my freedom and basically holding me hostage.

attributes.label: Names of the shopping district streets
attributes.characterDialogue: When we were <style="Link">shopping</style>, we noticed the weird names of the streets in the shopping district. It was so interesting. It looks like the streets are named after famous clothing items. What an interesting and smart way to name things. They were also some Shops named after famous dishes, like croissants for a <style="Link">coffee shop</style>. Discovering the weird naming conventions was sometimes actually fun, same for <style="Link">the beach</style>.

attributes.label: Duckling Lake
attributes.characterDialogue: The Duckling Lake. I read about it and was looking forward to seeing some <style="Link">Hot Boys</style>. Apparently swimming there is considered one of the <style="Link">Special Services</style> for the Cozy Camping Guests. The name <style="Link">is weird</style> again. But I’m guessing it’s the same as <style="Link">Platypus Beach</style>. But I mean it could also be one of those <style="Link">weird bird names</style> they chose for the pathways.

attributes.label: No sleep
attributes.characterDialogue: Yeah, I got no sleep there! The hotel we got <style="Link">Rejected</style> from would have been more to my standards! My body is a temple, and you don't place a temple on cheap foam matrasses! But besides that, I usually <style="Link">Wake Up</style>early and also<style="Link">Work Hard</style> and into the Night, and because of that I am simply not used to this mode of doing nothing, you know. Oh don't look at me like that. That is what it takes if you want to be as successful as me, my dear.

attributes.label: Gondolas
attributes.characterDialogue: Since the way up was already way <style="Link">too much walking</style> and finally was a gondola I was able to take. I of course jumped on the opportunity. <style="Link">The View</style> from the Gondola was surprisingly good, too.

attributes.label: Quality over Quantity
attributes.characterDialogue: I believe in "Quality over Quantity". I strive to stay a <style="Link">Lady of Class</style> and appreciate <style="Link">true Beauty</style>. Because of this I actually developed quite the fine taste, which not everyone can please. Especially not those <style="Link">awful restaurants</style>, I  was at in Misora.

attributes.label: Sickness
attributes.characterDialogue: On this Trip I was just constantly feeling sick, all of the time. It was probably this awful food from <style="Link">those restaurant</style>. And combine that with that <style="Link">scorching sun</style> at that <style="Link">annoying ocean</style> swinging me back and forth. Ugh I hated it.

attributes.label: Hiking / Mountain
attributes.characterDialogue: When I went up the mountain it was so annoying. The <style="Link">View was great</style>, but the path was just so long. I had to <style="Link">walk too much</style>. I would have loved to take the <style="Link">Cozy Camping Gondola</style>, but no. If I <style="Link">would have known</style>, I would have never gone up there.

attributes.label: Restaurant in the Evening
attributes.characterDialogue: In the evening, I went to this small Pizzeria, near our Hotel. Thought I could get some normal food there since there are <style="Link">No Meal</style> plans in the Hotel hah. And after the hike, I was very hungry. But it wasn't really a place for a <style="Link">Classy Lady</style> like me. It was very simple and bland but at least not as bad as the <style="Link">Seafood Restaurant</style>.

attributes.label: The scorching sun
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh, don't remind me. The sun was horrible. That much UV exposure is not good for my <style="Link">Beauty</style>. But it does help with <style="Link">Getting Up Early</style>, even though I usually get up before the sun rises.  But with all the heat that it brought, I wish we would have passed by the <style="Link">Duckling Lake</style>. I heard it is wonderful for bathing.

attributes.label: Classy Lady
attributes.characterDialogue: You know, everyone knows that I am just so special, <style="Link">rich</style> and perfect, and should be treated with the proper respect. Apparently, the entire city of Misora didn’t understand that. I was constantly rejected from entering <style="Link">parks</style> and <style="Link">hotels</style>. It unbelievable!

attributes.label: Her interest in vintage cars
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: She loves cars especially vintage ones, she's disappointed of Misora. She heard of a car colletion but they couldnt find one.

attributes.label: Discrimination
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: On the Trip she was discriminated against for being a woman, because she wasn't able to access certain attractions

attributes.label: Dolphin Tour
attributes.characterDialogue: The Dolphin Tour is a special <style="Link">Boat Tour</style> only for guest of <style="Link">Cozy Camping</style>. It leads directly to <style="Link">Duckling Lake</style>. She finds the <style="Link">naming conventions</style>

attributes.label: Annoying Husband
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh, you wanna know about Brandon? Uhm well, my husband was actually the one who wanted to go to Misora because of the <style="Link">Nature</style> here. Urgh I hate going into nature. It feels so primal. And then he also wanted to take the <style="Link">Bus</style> everywhere. It was so annoying. I couldn't even <style="Link">Sleep</style> the night before our trip because he was telling me about all the soo interesting things on the mountain. Why can't he be more into actually productive things? Urghh, sorry. Anyways, at least I got some peace at the <style="Link">Last Restaurant</style> that I went to. Let's talk about somethign else.

attributes.label: Hotel
attributes.characterDialogue:
Our day started with checking in to our small and simple Hotel. Im so glad that we took the <style="Link">Plane</style> and not the Train like my goofy husband suggested. He cares about the environment, but I'm more of a luxury person. 
However, he turned me so eco-friendly in Misora, haha. Right after we got to the Hotel  we took the local <style="Link">Bus</style> to get to a <style="Link">Coffee Shop</style>.

attributes.label: Too much walking
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: She had to walk way to much.

attributes.label: Fisherman
attributes.characterDialogue: I dont really like the <style="Link">Harbor</style>. It smells and is so dirty. But honestly those fisherman, I do respect! They <style="Link">Work Hard</style> and as you can see it pays off. They are clearly very rich people since they can effort all those boats. Maybe take an example in them?

attributes.label: Algea Bay
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: They saw it from the distance and decided it wasn't worth going to

attributes.label: Beauty
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh, thank you for noticing. My beauty is <style="Link">all natural</style> of course. <style="Link">Appearance</style> means a lot to me. That is how others see you, and you would only want them to see the best of you am I right?  <style="Link">Shopping</style> for these looks is not always that cheap, but it is worth it!

attributes.label: Spa
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: They were at a Spa in Misora

attributes.label: Hotel "Cozy Camping"
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: She is very glad she didn't stay at Cozy Camping,  They passed the Hotel and all of the Campers smelled horrible

attributes.label: The young generation
attributes.characterDialogue: Ah, this young generation... Always <style="Link">sleeping in</style>because they play <style="Link">video games</style> all day. I have a nephew, I know what I'm talking about.

attributes.label: Religious Sites
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: She is a fan of religious sites and they actually passed one in Misora, but there was a wedding happening so she couldn't enter.

attributes.label: Poor people
attributes.characterDialogue: You know, I think poverty is simply a mindset. All those poor people just dont <style="Link">Work Hard</style> enough. They should take an example on those <style="Link">Fisherman</style>. They at least work hard. Urgh, I am just not meant to be around poor people! That is also why I dont usually use  <style="Link">Public Transport</style>.

attributes.label: Holy Mario
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: They went past this weird statue, but she couldn't get a close look at it. It's a very weird statue with a very weird name. As an appreciator of real beauty she says she can live without buying it at the statue shop

attributes.label: The stuff she brought home
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: She brought a bunch of stuff home, her favourite piece is the dress they bought. Honestly she has bought so much stuff, she would have even bought out the museum if the stuff in there wasn't "Not for Sale"

attributes.label: Displaying Wealth
attributes.characterDialogue: Showing my wealth is very important for me! When you have the <style="Link">Money</style>, you should be able to show it. For example, I'm planning on building a <style="Link">Private Mansion</style>. Maybe on another island somewhere around here? Of course I don't always go that big. I can be humble too! For example the <style="Link">Gem Jewelery</style> that I bought in Misora already says a lot, doesnt it?

attributes.label: a shop for statues
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: They went to a premium souvenier shop of statues for the different memorials.  They didn't have names so she just picked the one which was prettiest, they also got a stone as a gift, which she is still confused by.

attributes.label: Video Games
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh yes video games, my nephew is always glued ot them and playing all day. I must admit, I've caught myself sneaking a few round of this racing game. Guess I'm still young at heart after all. You know, when I heard the name <style="Link">"Mario" in Misora</style>I thought I was gonna see the one from the video game, but instead it was just a boring old statue, which doesn't look like Mario at all.  They shouldn't have named it like that. It's so confusing. This city really was full of weird and confusing names.

attributes.label: City Info
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: They didnt receive as much info about the city as they would have liked, she complains that there wasn't any info point

attributes.label: Her plan for a private Mansion
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: As a fan of architecture her goal of course is to have her own private mansion and fill it with all the rare stuff she gathered. She plans to buy a second island.

attributes.label: Plankton Zoo
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :(

attributes.label: Museum of Modern Art
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: They saw it, but didn't go because "You can't buy the paintings there"

attributes.label: Friedas Garden Center
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: They passed it but didnt go, she also talk about a weird fact about it

attributes.label: House Plants
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: She loves houseplant, especially either really big ones or really small cute one's. She can put those in her mansion.  They saw a Garden Center but didnt go at the end. One has to set priorities.

attributes.label: She works hard
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: To become the important person she is now she needed to work hard, something which the poor people definitly dont know how to do

attributes.label: Gambling
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: Although she would have the money for it, she would never gamble. Gambling is just a scam and she doesn't understand why some people would go as far as to gamble their saving away. Just Stop, when you already spend to much. Then they don't have to be surprised if the can't effort anything anymore. She's glad she didn't have to look at one in Misora

attributes.label: Magpie Island
attributes.characterDialogue: Yes my private Island "Magpie Island" or how I like to call it "My kingdom". It's close to Misora. I love it! That's why I went, to check out the neighborhood. There is actually  <style="Link">Boat Tour</style> going to my island but I couldn't find where it started. Actually now that I think about it, I should get another!

attributes.label: Getting money stolen
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: The fear of getting all her money stolen is just so stressfull on her. Getting pickpocketed is just the worse, which is why they avoided the Fish and Crab Market in Misora. Aand that is also why she founded her company, to protect the people that need their money protected.

attributes.label: Getting scammed
attributes.characterDialogue: There are Scams everywhere, like this shitty excuse of a beach called "Algea Bay" in Misora. Or all of those dirty tricks that are used in Casinos. I'm sure you can't even win anything. But the biggest scam of all time is of course the moon landing. Fake all through

attributes.label: Working hard
attributes.characterDialogue: I feel like, working hard is a thing that the <style="Link">Young Generation</style> has forgotten about. But all they say is "Uhhhhh my 10 hours of sleep weeeeeee". They should get their shit together. Take me for an example. <style="Link">Working Hard</style> is my top priority and I dont care if i get <style="Link">No Sleep</style> because of it.

attributes.label: She is super important
attributes.characterDialogue: This node is sadly still missing :( here is a Summary: She is a woman of great importance and should be discriminated against like she was in Misora. She should have access to anywhere and others should work to respect the high position she is in

attributes.label: What her company does
attributes.characterDialogue: My company? You don't know what we do? We sell the very prestige service of offering people that need it to register their company on my private island and since it is declared as it's own country, I make the rules there. Which are "Do what you want" and "Don't pay any taxes". A much better enviroment to thrive than those horrible goverments.

But not for her, because she knows exactly where it is best invested in, her own beauty. As well as going shopping and finding the real quality products.

attributes.label: Cooling Water
attributes.characterDialogue: Oh, yeah some cooling water against that <style="Link">Scorching Sun</style> would have been nice. Maybe the hot guys at the <style="Link">Surf Club</style> could teach me how to surf, then I could cool down and do sports at the same time. That would be so perfect! Except for all the animals in the ocean, of course.

It's a shame there were no auctions running, she would have totally bought something there.

attributes.characterDialogue: Uhh, Children are the worst. They are so annoying. We actually chose not to stay at <style="Link">Cozy Camping</style>, because I heard there are a lot of children. attributes.characterDialogue: I should definitly get myself a second island. I already have a plan. I got "My Kingdom" during an auction, so I'm going to visit the upcoming auctions and wait for my chance to strike. I can usually sniff a good deal the moment I see it. Ahhh It's gonna be so amazing having a second island to show and inspire other people of how a successfull person looks like.

attributes.Clue/Filler: The feeling of being above the clouds is just different. It's beatiful honestly, you can really take in the view. I should also build my mansion high up

attributes.label: The horrible government
attributes.characterDialogue: This goverment? It is just horrible! Period. Firstly it completly discredits womanhood, by still allowing abortions. Like do they even realise how harmful abortions can be to woman. Like even offering me an abortion is basically saying "Your child should die and I will do that for you". Like do they think I'm not good enough to be a mother?  They also still haven't done anything against these climate activists, what if they destroy my painting with their tomato sauce? And even worse the are constantly wanting to steal my money and diguising it as taxes.
